.TH "zs_huge_class_size" 9 "zs_huge_class_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
zs_huge_class_size \- Returns the size (in bytes) of the first huge zsmalloc &size_class.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "size_t" zs_huge_class_size
.BI "(struct zs_pool *pool "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pool" 12
zsmalloc pool to use
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The function returns the size of the first huge class - any object of equal
or bigger size will be stored in zspage consisting of a single physical
page.
.SH "CONTEXT"
Any context.
.SH "RETURN"
the size (in bytes) of the first huge zsmalloc \fIsize_class\fP.
